<html>
  <problem>
    <title> CheckPoint: Work by many forces</title>

      <p>The diagram shows an object of unknown mass pulled by three forces with known magnitudes F<sub>1</sub>,
      F<sub>2</sub> and F<sub>3</sub>. The object undergoes a displacement 
      of magnitude \(s\) that makes an angle \(\theta\) with the force \(\vec{F}_{1}\).
      The three forces are perpendicular to each other:  \(\vec{F}_1 \perp \vec{F}_2 \perp \vec{F}_3\).
</p>
      <br/>

    <img src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK65.png" alt="BK65"/>
        <br/>

      <p>
Part 1. 
Find the work done by force \(\vec{F}_{1}\).
</p>

      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="no" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                Impossible to know without knowing the mass of the object 

          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">
                  \( F_1\cdot s \cdot \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">
                  \( (F_1-F_3) \cdot s \cdot \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">
                  \( \sqrt{(F_1-F_3)^2 +F_2^2 } \cdot s \cdot \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">
                  \( F_1 \cdot s \cdot \sin \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">
                  \( (F_1-F_3) \cdot s \cdot \sin \theta\)
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>


        <p>
Part 2. 
Find the work done by force \(\vec{F}_{2}\).
</p>

      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="yes" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                Impossible without knowing the mass of the object.

          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">
                  \( F_2\cdot s \cdot \sin \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">
                  \( - F_2\cdot s \cdot \sin \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">
                  \( F_2\cdot s \cdot \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">
                  \( - F_2\cdot s \cdot \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>


        <p>
Part 3. 
Find the work done by force \(\vec{F}_{3}\).
</p>

      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="no" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                Impossible to know without knowing the mass of the object 

          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">
                  \( F_3\cdot s \cdot \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">
                  \( (F_3-F_1) \cdot s \cdot \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="true">
                  \( - F_3 \cdot s \cdot \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">
                  \( (F_1-F_3) \cdot s \cdot \sin \theta\)
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>

      </problem>
</html>
